The evidence with the title 'Americans don't want senate's health care plan, but it's unclear ... ' says Jul 10, 2017  ... Only 17 percent of U.S. adults approve of the health care bill, according to a recent NPR/marist/PBS newshour poll.  ... Or to be more specific, they favor most Obamacare provisions  ... But not the individual mandate (which is needed to make the ACA work).  ... Obamacare was never a super-popular policy. 
